metadata.name: James Dean
metadata.description:
I told you it was the first time I had ever gone 
100 mph on a highway 
it was empty 
in Valentine 
I was shocked at how slow it felt 
I liked cruising at 80 

I wondered why I never let myself write prose 
or do the things I want to 

When we got back we covered our bed with 
a tarp & as the storm began & you were fixing 
the door to the tent a dog ran inside & came right to me 
child of Hecate 
his owners called him Bandit 
he was shaking 
so we let him sit out the weather with us 
we ate gas station chips 
I drink pop on vacation 
because I don’t drink 
that night we saw the lights 
I wish I knew how to describe them to you 
as anything other than alien 
or celestial, mining the land 
far far out west 
or were they waltzing 
1 would appear then 3       
then 6 then none then 1 
& all the locals said we hadn’t
even seen shit 
I thought about how I read
that James Dean became so fascinated 
with them that he demanded a telescope for his trailer on set 

& how he probably wrote prose
